    <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         HOW TO ADD A NEW RELEASE
         ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         1. Build a Release Archive in Xcode (Product → Archive)
         2. Export the app and create a DMG (e.g. WiredServer-X.Y.Z.dmg)
         3. Upload the DMG as a GitHub Release asset
         4. Sign the DMG:
              Pods/Sparkle/bin/sign_update WiredServer-X.Y.Z.dmg dsa_priv.pem
            → copy the printed Base64 string as sparkle:dsaSignature
         5. Get the file size in bytes:
              wc -c < WiredServer-X.Y.Z.dmg
         6. Add a new <item> below (copy the existing one and update all fields)
         ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

